<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5159696>
    dc:description "FIG. 7. — A-F, Murexsul hexagonus (Lamarck, 1816): A, B, ventral and dorsal views, lectotype (MHNG 1099/41/1); C, ventral view, paralectotype (MHNG 1099/41/2); D, ventral view, coll. BG, Cuba; E, ventral view, coll. DL, Saint-Barthélemy Island, 30-40 m deep; F, ventral view, coll. BG, Bimini, Bahama, 90 m deep. G, H, M. oxytatus (Smith, 1938): G, ventral view, paratype UF no. 5946, Caloosahatchee Formation, Plio-Pleistocene, Hendry County, Florida, photo courtesy of John Slapcinsky (UF); H, ventral view, coll. BG, Rosalind Bank, Honduras, on coral reef at 20 m deep. I, ventral view, M. zylmanae (Petuch, 1993), holotype CMNH no. 47379, Great Isaacs Cay,Bahamas,photo courtesy of M. Paustian (CMNH).J, ventral view,M. huberti (Radwin & D’Attilio, 1976),holotype SDNHM, no. 63078, west side of Grenada, West Indies, at 4.5 m deep, photo courtesy of Carole Hertz, Jim Berrian, Michael Wall and Paul Tuskes (SDNHM). K, ventral view,M. chesleri Houart, 2006, paratype MNHN no. 7008, Roatan Island,Honduras, on dead coral at 2 m deep.L, ventral view,M. sunderlandi (Petuch, 1987),holotype, USNM 859848,Cay Sal,Cay Sal Bank,Bahamas,under coral rubble at 10 m deep, photo courtesy of E. Strong (USNM). M, ventral view, M. warreni (Petuch,1993),holotype CMNH, Montego Bay,Jamaica, Greater Antilles, 20-30 m deep, photo courtesy of M. Paustan (CMNH). N, ventral view, M. jahami Merle & Garrigues, 2011, holotype MNHN.IM.24630, Peninsula Caravelle, Eastern Martinique. Scale bars: 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5159696/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5159706>
    dc:description "FIG. 12. — Morphology of spiral cords and denticles: A, Pygmaepterys pointieri n. sp., holotype MNHN-IM-2013-8488, Gosier Island, at 6 m deep; B, P. karukerensis n. sp., holotype MNHN IM-2000-27730, Pigeon Island, at 50 m deep; C, Lindapterys domlamyi n. sp., holotype MNHN IM-2000-27732; D, Muricopsis guadalupensis n. sp., holotype MNHN IM-2000-27731, Malendure, Guadeloupe, at 10 m deep; E, Murexsul hexagonus (Lamarck, 1816), lectotype (MHNG 1099/41/1). Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars: 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5159706/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5159698>
    dc:description "FIG. 8. — Map showing the geographic range of Murexsul hexagonus (Lamarck,1816) and Murexsul oxytatus (Smith, 1938).Symbols: Â, M. hexagonus; , M. oxytatus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5159698/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7191403>
    dc:description "FIG. 9. — Scatterplot showing the relationship between the length of the siphonal canal (×2) and the total shell length in Murexul hexagonus and in Murexsul oxytatus (Smith,1938).Symbols:¿, Murexsul oxytatus; ¢, Murexsul hexagonus Lamarck,1816;—, Linéaire (Murexsul oxytatus; --, Linéraire (Murexsul hexagonus)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7191403/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

